==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neonomian
<hw>Ne`o*no"mi*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Neo-</ets>
+ Gr. <?/ law.]</ety> <def>One who advocates adheres to new laws; esp.
one who holds or believes that the gospel is a new law.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neonomian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Neonomian
<hw>Ne`o*no"mi*an</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to the
Neonomians, or in accordance with their doctrines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neonomianism</ent>⟦br⟧
